              It is a structural analog of LSD, distinguished by the presence of a propionyl group attached to the indole nitrogen.
              Due to its close structural relationship with LSD, ALD-52, and 1B-LSD, 1P-LSD is frequently examined in chemical
              research involving lysergic acid derivatives. Researchers have studied its stability, potential degradation pathways,

              It is structurally similar to the naturally occurring alkaloid found in psilocybin mushrooms, differing only by the presence
              of an acetoxy group. Due to its close relationship with other tryptamines, it has been studied in the field of forensic and

More About Us 9 Years Experience In Researching Nootropics Shop Research‑Grade Nootropics Online Research-Grade Reagents & Reference Materials Skip the hype; get traceable lab materials. Euro-Nootropics supplies analytical-grade reagents and reference standards for method development, calibration, and QC. Each lot is identity-verified (HPLC/LC-MS, NMR/FTIR, where applicable), issued with a Certificate of Analysis (CoA) and SDS , and labeled per REACH/CLP for clean audit trails. Our catalog spans heterocyclics, amino-derivatives, cholinergic probes, and other research tools—curated for consistency and documentation , not consumer use. We prioritize transparency : batch numbers, purity specs, and test methods are disclosed so you can reproduce results and compare across studies. If a compound doesn’t meet our release criteria, it doesn’t ship. Why Choose Euro Nootropics? – Quality You Can Trust Unmatched Purity and Transparency At Euro Nootropics, quality isn’t a buzzword – it’s a promise. We work with reputable manufacturers who adhere to strict quality control procedures, then subject every batch of product to independent testing using techniques such as High‑Performance Liquid Chromatography (HPLC) and Mass Spectrometry. The result? Compounds that are consistently high in purity and free from impurities. Unlike many vendors who hide behind vague claims, we publish our test results. You can browse product pages and see the COA for yourself. If you ever have a question about a batch, our team is ready to provide answers. Customer‑Focused Service Our relationship with customers doesn’t end at checkout. We know buying cognitive enhancers can be confusing, especially if you’re new to the world of nootropics. That’s why we offer personalized support. Have a question about which product best fits your study or research aim? Looking for suggestions on stacking compounds? Need help tracking a shipment? Our friendly customer service team is here to help. We respond promptly and strive to exceed expectations. In short, we treat you the way we’d like to be treated. Innovation and Continual Improvement The field of nootropics evolves quickly, and so do we. Our team of scientists and researchers is constantly reviewing new studies and exploring novel compounds. We also listen carefully to feedback from our customers. If there’s a product you’d like to see in our store or information you want added, let us know. Many of our latest offerings are the direct result of customer requests and emerging research. By partnering with Euro Nootropics, you’re aligning yourself with a company that values progress and is committed to bringing you the most effective, safe and innovative supplements on the market. What Are Our Materials Used For? Cellular Bioenergetics Used as reference materials to calibrate assays quantifying ATP production, mitochondrial membrane potential, and metabolic flux (e.g., respirometry/Seahorse™ workflows). Suitable for method development and QC in cell-free and cell-based systems. Neurochemical Systems Research Employed as ligands or analytical standards to interrogate receptor binding, transporter kinetics, and enzyme pathways (e.g., AChE/MAO/COMT) in cell lines, tissue homogenates, or purified targets . Vascular Physiology & Microcirculation Models For bench studies of endothelial signaling (NO/eNOS), barrier transport (e.g., BBB models), and perfusion phantoms . Useful in method validation , biomarker panel development, and chromatographic assay optimization. Neural Signal Analysis & Oscillations Materials to benchmark protocols that examine synaptic parameters and oscillatory metrics in slices or computational pipelines (e.g., spectral power, coherence). Neuroprotection & Redox Chemistry Applied in oxidative-stress paradigms (ROS/RNS readouts), antioxidant capacity assays (ORAC/FRAP), and cell-death markers (caspase/TUNEL). Supports positive/negative control sets and inter-lab comparability. Neurodevelopment & Plasticity Markers Used to quantify expression of neurogenesis and plasticity markers (e.g., BDNF, DCX, GAP-43 ) in non-clinical models. Suitable for qPCR/ELISA/western blot normalization and assay performance verification . If you’re conducting research on neurodegenerative diseases or simply want to support long‑term brain health, this category is a must‑visit. You’ll find powders and solutions that blend seamlessly into your existing regimen, whether you’re studying them in isolation or stacking them with other compounds. With Euro Nootropics, you can trust that every neuroprotective compound has been tested for purity and potency. Cholinergics If memory and learning are your priorities, look no further than our cholinergic collection. Kiwi is your own International online pharmacy. We are proud to offer many popular drugs, medicines and general healthcare items at fantastic competitive pharmacy prices. Kiwi is a secure online shopping site that uses the best encryption software and you can be safe in the knowledge that Kiwi is backed by a network of successful pharmacies in New Zealand, Australia, United Kingdom, the USA, Canada and India. Seeing an opportunity to provide quality, cheaper over-the-counter pharmacy products globally our Internet pharmacy was created and has been keeping international customers satisfied since its inception. How can I be sure Kiwi is legitimate? Kiwi initially operated solely from a large New Zealand pharmacy store that has been established for over 40 years. As a New Zealand pharmacy, we are members of the Pharmaceutical Society of New Zealand and the Pharmacy Guild of New Zealand. Our pharmacists are registered with the Pharmacy Council of New Zealand. Our pharmacy is audited on a regular basis by Medsafe (the New Zealand medicines control authority), in accordance with the laws of operating a New Zealand pharmacy. You can be safe in the assurance that our pharmacy has passed all the requirements of the Medsafe authority.

Our pharmacists are members of the Pharmaceutical Society of New Zealand. The Pharmaceutical Society is the professional body for New Zealand pharmacists. The Society provides professional support, education, training and career development for all pharmacists, assisting and enabling them to deliver best practice and professional services for the public.

As we are a full retail and dispensing pharmacy, we are also members of the Pharmacy Guild of New Zealand. The Pharmacy Guild provides member pharmacies and pharmacists with a diverse range of services designed to support and enhance the commercial and professional interests of community pharmacy.

In order to become a qualified pharmacist in New Zealand, there is a requirement of a minimum of four years University study, followed by a full year of on-site training. Only once the trainee intern is fully appraised at the end of this fifth year (by means of practical examinations), can they be certified as a qualified pharmacist. All pharmacists in New Zealand must undergo continuing education, meaning that they must continue to actively learn and study during their career as a pharmacist.

Our affiliate pharmacies are all licensed and regulated pharmacies in their jurisdiction and their service and support is guaranteed. title: ZellBio GmbH
content: Category: For Researchers. Content: Home - ZellBio GmbH Call: +49(0)7336 2279990 | Email: info[at]zellbio.com 0 Items Select Page Luciferin-Bioluminescence Bioluminescence is the production and emission of light by a living organism. Bioluminescence occurs widely in marine vertebrates and invertebrates, as well as in some fungi, microorganisms and terrestrial invertebrates. Luciferin, the firefly substrate of luciferase, is a common reagent used throughout the biotechnology field. The injection of luciferin allows for the real-time, noninvasive monitoring of disease progression and/or drug efficacy in these model systems through Bioluminescence Imaging (BLI). Discover more! No. | CAS No. × Agarose Resins Antibiotics & Antimicrobials Biochemical Reagents Bioluminescence Biological Buffers Cell Culture Plant & Research Media Additives Detergents & Membrane Agents DNA Amplification Enzymes, Inhibitors & Substrates Plant Growth Regulators Protein Expression & Purification IPTG IPTG is an analog of galactose that is nonmetabolizable and inactivates the lac repressor to induce synthesis of β-galactosidase in E. coli. The expression of cloned genes under the control of the lac operon is induced by IPTG. IPTG is often used in the induction of recombinant proteins, is a substrate for thigalactoside transacetylase and has been reported to induce penicillinase in bacteria. IPTG is commonly used in cloning procedures that require induction of β-galactosidase and is most often used with X-Gal for blue/white bacterial colony screening. Order now! IPTG Stock Solution from ZellBio GmbH on Vimeo . IPTG Stock Stability & Storage from ZellBio GmbH on Vimeo . Higher Performance & Simplicity in One Disposable Cassette. Patent-protected thin-film cassettes provide highly accurate, repeatable cell counts and cell size analysis in under 15 seconds. Inspired by the gold-standard Coulter Principle used in high-end counting systems worldwide, the Moxi cassette flows thousands of cells per test through a cell sensing zone to accurately capture the impedance-based volumetric measurement of each individual cell in the sample. Discover more! Healthcare, pharmaceutical and industrial organizations rely on quality-assured prepared media. Maintaining cleanrooms and other aseptic areas to the most stringent regulations, plus validating sterility testing processes, requires quality assured prepared culture media. The EU GMP Annex 1 highlights an increasing need for organisations operating in pharmaceutical and medical device manufacture, and other industrial sectors, to reduce the risk of contamination wherever possible. Discover more! BioAssay Kits Molecular Biology Plant Research Oxidative stress & Antioxidants Oxidative stress, as one of the most common types of toxicity, is defined by an imbalance between the generation of reactive oxygen species (ROS) and the ability of biological systems to detoxify ROS or its related damage. Many types of chemical, physical, and microbial agents can potentially induce oxidative-mediated stress in cells and tissues by damaging the biological components, including proteins, lipids, and DNA. Hot Products / In Stock High Quality Competitive Pricing Technical Support Explore Featured Products CATALYSTS AND LIGANDS Catalysts are substances that accelerate chemical reactions without being consumed and are fundamental tools for chemical engineers. 01 MATERIALS SCIENCE Material science chemicals are compounds designed to facilitate the creation and exploration of novel materials across diverse applications. 02 BIOACTIVE REAGENTS A bioactive reagent is a compound that act as regulators of biological functions and thus can be candidate compounds for pharmaceuticals. 03 BUILDING BLOCKS Building blocks are chemicals and reagents used in laboratories to perform syntheses, analyses, and other research. 04 INHIBITORS/AGONISTS Inhibitors and agonists are compounds that can bind to proteins, such as enzymes, leading to either a decrease or activation of their activity. 05 OTHERS Miscellaneous chemicals contribute to the broader landscape of chemical innovation and serves as a hub for versatile chemical solutions. 06 About EvitaChem EvitaChem was created to take responsibility for both manufacturing and sourcing to help researchers and others to obtain high-quality compounds and chemical building blocks. Our goal is to simplify the searching and purchasing process for you and remove needless logistic and paperwork hurdles. Customer satisfaction is our priority put your needs first and go above and beyond to provide customized support.
